{
  "texts": [
    "For simplicity, we do not consider different types of underlying quality, such as methodological or theoretical novelty 3,65.",
    "Fit denotes the substantive usefulness of paper i for agent j, represented by fit i,j.",
    "Fit is expected to vary across agents due to differences in topic or preferences, i.e., agents may choose not to read even a terrific paper if it is on too unrelated a topic.",
    "For homogeneous agents, fit i,j = 0. fit i,j will raise or lower the quality q i,j of paper i in agent j's eyes as in Eq.",
    "( 1):q i, j = q i + fit i, jð1Þ• Perception error: represented by ε i,j."
  ]
}